    "title": "AI & Robotics Snacks — April 13, 2026",
    "date": "2026-04-13",
    "tags": ["Claude Mythos", "Project Glasswing", "VC funding Q1 2026", "Locus Array", "Anvil Robotics"],
    "fresh": true,
    "content": "**AI & Robotics Snacks** — April 13, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 🔐 Anthropic Built the Most Powerful AI Ever and Is Not Letting You Near It\n\nAnthropic released Claude Mythos Preview — its most capable model by every metric — and immediately announced it won't be made publicly available, due to what the company describes as \"cybersecurity risks.\"\n\n- **The benchmarks:** 93.9% on SWE-bench Verified (up from 80.8%), 97.6% on USAMO 2026. During testing, Mythos autonomously discovered and exploited zero-day vulnerabilities in every major OS and browser — including a 27-year-old bug in OpenBSD.\n- **The access plan:** Project Glasswing — 50+ tech organizations, $100M in usage credits, restricted consortium only. Available on Google Vertex AI and Amazon Bedrock. Not available to you.\n\n*The most capable AI model ever built finds zero-days in every operating system and then Anthropic decides, actually, let's not release this one.*\n\n**Sources:** [InfoQ](https://www.infoq.com/news/2026/04/anthropic-claude-mythos/) | [NxCode](https://www.nxcode.io/resources/news/claude-mythos-preview-anthropic-most-powerful-model-2026) | [NBC News](https://www.nbcnews.com/tech/security/anthropic-project-glasswing-mythos-preview-claude-gets-limited-release-rcna267234)\n\n---\n\n## 💸 Q1 2026: VCs Put $300 Billion Into Startups and 80% of It Went to AI\n\nVenture capital had the biggest quarter in recorded history in Q1 2026 — $300 billion raised globally — and $242 billion of that went to AI companies.\n\n- **The numbers:** OpenAI alone raised $122B. Anthropic: $30B. xAI: $20B. Waymo: $16B. Together those four rounds represent 65% of all global venture investment in the quarter.\n- **The framing:** Investors are now treating foundation model companies as \"critical national infrastructure.\" That's the framing. The actual business models remain, generously, in development.\n\n*OpenAI raised $122 billion in a single quarter and is still losing more than it makes. The math is not the point.*\n\n**Sources:** [Crunchbase](https://news.crunchbase.com/venture/record-breaking-funding-ai-global-q1-2026/) | [Crunchbase Sector](https://news.crunchbase.com/venture/foundational-ai-startup-funding-doubled-openai-anthropic-xai-q1-2026/)\n\n---\n\n## 🏭 Locus Robotics Launched a Fully Autonomous Warehouse. No Hands Required.\n\nLocus Robotics unveiled Locus Array — a fully autonomous fulfillment system that combines mobile robotics, a robotic picking arm, and AI-powered perception to complete end-to-end warehouse workflows without manual intervention.\n\n- **What's new:** Unlike pick-assist robots that work alongside humans, Locus Array handles the full workflow. Early deployments are live in North America, with Europe and APAC scale-up planned.\n- **The signal:** \"Fully autonomous\" has been a warehouse PR promise for a decade. Actual deployments at scale are a different thing. Locus says those are happening.\n\n**Sources:** [RoboticsTomorrow](https://www.roboticstomorrow.com/news/2026/04/13/locus-robotics-launches-locus-array-a-new-class-of-physical-ai-robotics-for-fully-autonomous-fulfillment/26397/)\n\n---\n\n## 🧱 \"Legos for Robots\" Raised $5.5 Million. Eight Months Old.\n\nAnvil Robotics, which describes its platform as \"Legos for robots\" for physical AI teams, raised a $5.5M seed round from Matter Venture Partners and Humba Ventures — eight months after founding.\n\n- **The pitch:** Modular, composable hardware components that let robotics teams build custom physical AI platforms without starting from scratch each time.\n- **The context:** Robotics startup funding hit nearly $14B in 2025, up from $8.2B in 2024. In 2026, humanoid robotics alone is projected to draw $20B+. Someone is going to supply the building blocks.\n\n*Eight months old, $5.5M in the bank, and the pitch is \"Legos for robots.\" The 2020s are a strange decade.*\n\n**Sources:** [Crunchbase](https://news.crunchbase.com/robotics/physical-ai-custom-robot-builder-seed-funding-anvil/)"
  }
